metadata.name: Ceremony #226
metadata.description:
This series celebrates fxhash turning one. #fxhashturnsone

I‚Äôm so grateful for this place and have ho idea how to adequately articulate how much this platform has changed my life, but it has. A million thanks to the team. You are so appreciated as are the artists and collectors that have made this such a beautiful community. ü•Ç

Definitely check out ‚ÄúForever‚Äù mode by tapping ‚ÄúF‚Äù or mouse click/tap ‚Äî it will animate (you guessed it) forever and will change its layout every 365 frames, in honor of this wonderful year, and every year after. Some forever modes will ‚Äúnever forget‚Äù and others will fade as they progress. No idea if that‚Äôs a metaphor but it is a trait, that much I know.

All primary sales are donated to Code/Art, which is a charity that uses ‚Äú‚Ä¶Art to Inspire Girls in Computer Science.‚Äù Read about Code/Art here: https://www.code-art.com/

Ceremony uses public domain art (which is the original, more implicit version CC0) made exclusively by women.

See fxtext article linked from the project page for a gallery of the source material and other notes.

Ceremony is also CC0, so feel free use anything here in other projects.

You can read more about CC0 here:
https://creativecommons.org/share-your-work/public-domain/cc0/

F : ‚ÄúForever‚Äù mode (tap after initial render completes)
P : Pause/Play
(mouse click/tap also works to start ‚ÄúForever‚Äù mode or Pause/Play)

A : Add Grain (only works when paused in ‚ÄúForever‚Äù mode.)
G : Toggle Grain (resets the whole piece)
M : Toggle Matte (resets the whole piece)

S : Save Image
1 -> 6 : Set pixel density (resets the whole piece)
(Default pixel density is 1 @ 2000x2000)

If you want to start in "Forever" mode, you can append "&forever=true" to the url in the live view.
You can also add pixel density to the url by appending ‚Äú&density=2‚Äù (or 3, 4, etc) to have it render at higher resolutions by default.

metadata.name: Gammalt #81
metadata.description:
Celebrating getting old with Fx(hash).

Save as png:
Click ‚Äús‚Äù
or double click/tap

Resolution:
Default image width = 2000px and aspect ratio = 4:3.
Modify the image width between 2000px and 10000px by adding ‚Äú&w=xxxx‚Äù to the url (e.g. &w=4000).
High resolutions are computationally expensive and may take a while.

Background:
The canvas background texture is visible by default. This can be toggled off by adding ‚Äú&b=0‚Äù to the url.
The background scales with resolution to mimic a bigger canvas so it will look different at different resolutions.
At high resolutions a Moir√© pattern may appear on the canvas background texture due to the way images are resized in the browser. It‚Äôs always recommended to download a full resolution version of the piece.

By KRANKARTA
Created on Firefox desktop 105.0 on 2022-11-11 in javascript and GLSL.

metadata.name: meios #253
Bricks & Books #46
metadata.description:
Civil engineering and reading, two passions, two disciplines, numbers and letters. Construction and literature, two vocations so different and yet with such close souls.
They are both represented here by Bricks and Books paying a symbolic tribute to construction and literature in one collection.
The challenge was keeping them together in the same piece of code to be able to maintain the strength of the message and the aesthetic of the creation.

metadata.name: Stacking I - Genuary Edition #29
metadata.description:
This year's Genuary has been so much fun and alongside, I have been working on making my "Stacking" collection generative. 

The Genuary32 event is the ideal time to showcase what I have produced. 
This is the first in a series of five Stacking Tokens.

Features:
8 Different color palettes including 4 taken from the Studio Yorktown Color Town Hall:
Benelit - Esquisse - Maneki - Stockholm Lollipop (Studio Yorktown)
Jasmin - Retro - Neon - St Kilda (P1xelboy)

5 Different configurations:
Centred Tower
Duo Grid
Trio Grid
Left Hand Tower
Right Hand Tower

Made in P5.js by P1xelboy - February 2023
Special thanks to Studio Yorktown for creating the Color Townhall.

metadata.name: Lands #69
metadata.description:
Lands are a group of artworks creating a minimalist and abstract satellite view. The earth is changing, more and more, day after day, the satellite views are a great proof of that. Stay aware and be careful is important.

I wanted to representing something real, linked with my values, and keep a beautiful composition and colors harmony.‚Ä® I worked with a new fresh touch for the colors management.

The size, position and frequency of the pieces are generated for each token, along with the color theme. 

Features : 
- piecesCount : the number of circles and rectangles.
- glitchLinesCount :  the number of lines behind the shapes.
- MultipleGlitchDirections : if the directions of the lines behind are just horizontal or vertical, or both (10% of chance to have only one direction)‚Ä®.

‚Ä®Handmade by code with Javascript, made with fragment.tools
‚Ä®Quentin Hocd√©, Brussels (Belgium), 2023.

metadata.name: Disdain #27
metadata.description:
Disdain ‚Äî "The feeling that someone or something is unworthy of one's consideration or respect"

This is a project created for the #Genuary32nd minting party. 
Based on my entry for #Genuary26, the prompt was "My Kid Could Have Done That". 
It‚Äôs also my first project published on fxhash!

The idea behind it was to replicate drawings made by my kids but give it some refined composition and colour selection so that it could pass as a "real" artist‚Äôs piece.

Press "s" key to save it as a PNG image.

metadata.name: Broken Angles #26
metadata.description:
Angles represent the artist's view of the space and the visible subject, and the position is chosen so that the audience is able to see the subject from that angle.
The angles determine the audience's point of view in this way and by changing the angles, the audience can see the subject of the image from a new perspective.
Made by p5.js
